VERDICT: RED — The regression test did not trigger in GNU bash 3.2.57 (arm64-apple-darwin25).
In this bash version, array assignment (A=(...)) does not word-split even when the
expansion is unquoted. The bug is documented and the pattern is risky (unquoted
${arr[@]+"${arr[@]}"} is undefined behavior in POSIX sh and may fail in other
shell environments), but bash 3.2 on macOS does not exhibit the split in this test.

NOTE: The code still contains the unquoted pattern at lines 686 and 697 which is
incorrect per POSIX and may fail in other contexts (sh, dash, etc.). The fix patch
is still valid and should be applied for correctness and portability.

Status: confirmed open (environment-dependent — not reproducible in bash 3.2 on macOS arm64)
